==Demographics==
As of the 2023 census from the ACS, Presque Isle Harbor has a population of 722, from which 100% are citizens, with the median age of 65.8. The largest ethnic group in Presque Isle Harbor are white (99.4%), with the rest of the population being mixed (0.554%).

Out of 722 people, 219 people in Presque Isle Harbor were employed. The largest form of business in this community is the finance industry, with 41 people working at that sector, and the highest paying industry is in the construction sector. <ref>{{Cite web |title=Presque Isle Harbor, MI {{!}} Data USA |url=https://datausa.io/profile/geo/presque-isle-harbor-mi/ |access-date=2026-01-24 |website=datausa.io |language=en}}</ref>{{US Census population
